@Justin_Montois We will definitely check when we have our next practice session.

@s-neff I forgot to mention in my post that I did change the current limit to 60A for our elimination matches, which did not seem to make any noticeable difference to the problem. We will definitely check the health of each drive motor, and try measuring temperature after practices. We let our driver use the whole drivetrain as well.

@nuttle We have unused batteries that we can try, but I would be surprised if all of our batteries had the same problem at the same time, since their ages vary quite a bit. Our battery beak reports a normal internal resistance.

All motors on our robot are Falcon 500s. The failure is unusually low battery voltage during a match with no obvious explanation from driverstation logs or Phoenix SignalLogger files.
